ord><keyword weight="0.4365">Distributed computing</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>Compositional state space generation means the generation of a condensed version of the state space of a system in a compositional manner. The system is divided to parts. The state spaces of the parts are generated, condensed and composed to get a state space of the system. The method may be applied recursively; that is, the state spaces of the parts may have been generated compositionally. The generated condensed state space is in a certain sense equivalent with the ordinary state space, thus it can be used for the analysis of certain properties of the system.</abstract></paper>